1.	Why do you need an AI agent when AWS already has Auto Scaling?
They want to test whether your system adds value beyond built-in automation.
Good answer idea:
•	Auto Scaling reacts to single metrics
•	AI agent can correlate multiple signals
•	Logs + metrics + events
•	Perform root cause analysis
Example:
CPU spike may be due to
CPU spike occurs
Auto Scaling logic:
IF CPU > 70%
→ Add instance
But the spike might be caused by:
•	database connection bottleneck
•	memory leak
•	bad deployment
•	traffic anomaly
•	misconfigured cache
•	Auto Scaling just adds instances, while AI diagnoses the real issue.
The agent correlates metrics from CloudWatch, logs from S3, and historical incidents from DynamoDB, then uses reasoning through Amazon Bedrock to identify patterns and determine the most likely root cause before triggering remediation
